net.sf.mmm.util.metakey.api

Interface MetakeyCore

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    MetakeyAudioVideo, MetakeyGraphics, MetakeyId3v2, MetakeyMovie, MetakeyMultimedia, MetakeyMusic, MetakeyOffice

    public interface MetakeyCore
    This interface is a collection of constants defining keys for metadata-properties.
    This is the root that all such interfaces inherit from. It defines the common properties and is inspired by but NOT identical to the DCMI.
    All properties defined by this interface and its sub-interfaces by default have values of the type String. Exceptions will be documented explicitly in the javadoc.
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)

      • LANGUAGE

        static final String LANGUAGE
        The (main) language of the content according to RFC-4646. Typically a two letter code according to ISO-639-1 that may be optionally followed by hyphen and two-letter code according to ISO-3166. The case of the letters does NOT matter. However a common practice is to use lower-case for language-codes and upper-case for country-codes.
        Examples are "en" or "fr-CA".
        Will NOT be set if NOT applicable (e.g. for an symbolic image or instrumental music).
        URI: http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/language
        DCMI Name: language
        DCMI Definition: A language of the resource.
        DCMI URI: http://purl.org/dc/terms/language
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
